name: Naked
jacob_blurb: This was giving misogyny and rape apology for me. The few pseudointellectual rants in between didn't win me over. Did I miss some nuance? I couldn't tell you, I was too pissed off. I did read an interview or two with Leigh and he certainly didn't change my mind.

name: Ali: Fear Eats the Soul
jacob_blurb: This is a perfect film for me. Every frame a masterpiece. A haunting story that made me think and feel new things. Thank you for being you, Fassbinder!

name: The Love Witch
jacob_blurb: Biller epitomizes the aurteur. She makes writer/directors seem like underachievers. In Love Witch, she's writing and perfoming the music, designing and sewing the costumes. If you see a painting in a scene, she made it. The homage to technicolor is right on the money. I like to be challenged and our senses of humor are too similar, so I dinged it half a point. But Biller is GOAT 1000/10

name: Mishima: A Life in Four Chapters
The Passion of Joan of Arc
Valerie and Her Week of Wonders
A Girl Walks Home Alone at Night
The Color of Pomegranates
jacob_blurb: This was definitely a challenging film. It felt a bit like reading an unfamiliar style of poetry. But while the meaning of certain scenes could be elusive, the visual experience was absolutely stunning. Combined with its poetic narrative, this made Pomegranates one of the most unique, mesmerizing experiences I've had with a film.
trophy_notes:
Andy gets a Special Connection Award for his Parajanov-Vartanov award
Joey gets a Bad Boy trophy for having a lot of work to do.
